description:
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for an individual who enjoys working with children, young people and their families. This stimulating and challenging role will offer the post holder the opportunity to work as part of a team to provide nursing and personal care to children and young people with complex health needs, who may also be dependent upon medical technology. The work involves working in partnership with families in the own homes and occasionally other settings e.g. Hospice, Hospital or Short Breaks Unit. A willingness and ability to travel is essential.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The post holder will be working within the Paediatric Homecare Team based in Mid Cornwall and full training will be given. This post is to cover a variable shift pattern, including nights, weekends and split day shifts.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Experience of working with children, young people and families in a health, social care or education setting is essential. The ideal candidate will have previous experience of working with children who have nursing and medical needs.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a 25 hours per week post.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Annette Swiggs, Home Care Manager on 01872 221443&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameLinda BibbyJob titleClinical LeadEmail addressl.bibby@nhs.netTelephone number07789777412&lt;/p&gt;
